    "narrative": "For the April 16th slate, the Zurich Zebras\u2019 lineup is anchored by **Yordan Alvarez**, who represents our strongest play with a 65.44 score. Despite facing a respectable arm in Mejia, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from an elite xwOBA profile and a favorable platoon setup, making him a must-start as he anchors the heart of the order. **Junior Caminero** (59.78) and **Gary Sanchez** (58.68) also provide significant utility; **Gary Sanchez** is particularly interesting today, as he draws a positive matchup against Corbin, allowing his raw power to overcome mediocre park factors and boost his efficiency rating well above his baseline.\n\nPlatoon edges remain a primary driver of our configuration, with **Dillon Dingler** (55.99) serving as the most beneficiaries of matchup-based optimization. By leveraging the dynamic platoon advantage against Bubic, **Dillon Dingler** earns a spot over alternatives who lack such distinct lane advantages. The most difficult decision on the bench involved **Josh Smith**, who finished with a 39.60 rating\u2014just shy of our 40.0 \"Zebras Floor.\" While **Josh Smith** usually provides a stable ceiling, his negative platoon split against Lopez and a deep lineup placement (#8) forced him to the bench in favor of higher-leverage opportunities elsewhere.\n\nRisk management remains a priority for the front office, particularly with **Yordan Alvarez** currently holding a \"Lineup Pending\" status; we have projected him into the #2 spot, but any shift lower in the order could marginally dampen his output. Elsewhere, we continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains sidelined on the IL, while **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Kyle Schwarber** are out of commission due to today's team off-days. We will look for **Trea Turner**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Colt Keith**, **Zac Veen**, **Victor Scott II**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, and **Luis Pena** to maintain readiness as we navigate the scarcity of stolen bases and optimize our remaining game caps. **Kazuma Okamoto** (52.14) and **Chase Meidroth** (49.85) complete the active group, providing necessary stability against Sproat and Matz, respectively.",
